Package dog.giraffe.image.transform

Image transformations.
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Cluster2.Projection
    Contains all the information to classify and transform pixels.
    Mask
    Describes masks that can be applied to clustering algorithms to disregard data points.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Cluster1
    Clusters the pixel of an image and replaces every pixel with a color assigned to pixel's nearest center.
    Cluster2
    Clusters the pixel of an image and replaces every pixel with a color assigned to pixel's nearest center.
    Hue
    Hue transforms an RGB image to the HSV color space and selects the hue components as its sole output component.
    HyperHue
    A transformation replacing every pixel of an image with its hyper-hue.
    Intensity
    A transformation the replaces every pixel of the input image with its euclidean length.
    Normalize
    Normalizes the range of the components of an image.
    NormalizedDifferenceVegetationIndex
    A transformation replacing every pixel of an input image with the normalized difference vegetation index of the first two components.
    NormalizedHyperHue
    NormalizedHyperHue transforms an image as HyperHue does and than normalizes all the vectors to have a uniform length.
    Select
    A transformation which select components of an input image.
